Do you have an opinion on the development, build, or deployment of Discover projects?

properties.description: (It's fine if you don't)

fields.title: Over the following questions, I'll ask your happiness scale for our projects. \*Rate the lowest score depending on the project.\*

properties.description: So, if you're 5/5 happy for the help center, and 1/5 for the public site, put 1/5 and explain why after. Make sense?

fields.title: Cool! First question. How happy are you with the technologies we're currently using?

properties.description: We're using Wordpress for the public site, blog, and Wordpress with Angular.js in the help center. We're using Gatsby for the developer portal.

fields.title: What would you change about our technologies, {{field:d824a0e7-5e57-4291-b46d-5a337974259b}}?
Second question. How happy are you with the build tools we're using?

properties.description: In the public site and blog, we're using Gulp, SASS, and concatenating scripts. In Gatsby, the build tooling is based on Webpack and styled components.

fields.title: What would you change about builds, {{field:d824a0e7-5e57-4291-b46d-5a337974259b}}?
Third question. How happy are you with our codebase?

properties.description: In the public site and blog, we're using jQuery and jQuery plugins. We use Angular in the Help center. We use React and npm modules in the developer portal.

fields.title: What would you change about our codebase, {{field:d824a0e7-5e57-4291-b46d-5a337974259b}}?
Fourth question. How happy are you with our deployment processes?

properties.description: For the public site, blog and help center, we merge into master, manually preview on preprod, and manually deploy (owned by Paulina). In the developer portal, we use CI to run tests, get previews, and automatic deployment upon merging to master.

fields.title: What would you change about out deployment, {{field:d824a0e7-5e57-4291-b46d-5a337974259b}}?

answers.text: This is a strange question. Should the technology make me happy or it should serve a purpose well :P?
As a first step I would standardise frontend tooling and development environment setup across all the Wordpress sites so that changing between projects is a seamless as possible.

I have other starter questions:
- how well do our technologies support Typeform customers?
- how well do our technologies support our internal stakeholders?
- what is it about our current stack that is stopping us achieving business goals?
- if you had one vote to fix one thing in our stack, what would it be?
- what are the biggest technical challenges Discover will face in the next year?
I would make sure deployment and rollback is standardised across all sites so we can have "proper" control of deployments.

metadata.user_agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_12_6) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/60.0.3112.101 Safari/537.36

answers.text: I would add easier rollback and previews on all our sites. CI everywhere would be nice.
Unless we don't change technology, we cannot change gulp/scss to something newer. The current state is not troubling for me.

I'd get rid of Angular. Of course I'd decouple Wordpress from our projects. But it's a huuuuge change. And even if we do it, we'd still need to use WP on server side, e.g. when adding new types of sites etc. so we'll just get rid of it from rendering. I suppose we're not thinking about some React/Node CMS. It's too big.

I'd remove Angular. I'd remove jQuery too, but it's still strongly connected to the fact that we have WP and unless we switch to some server side generating tool, there's no point to remove jQuery in exchange to e.g. React.

Here's a joke: 
What is the fastest country in the world? 






Russia

metadata.user_agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_11_6) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/60.0.3112.113 Safari/537.36

answers.text: Everything we want to achieve should be doable, we just need to make a plan and allocate time to do it :)
As an overall technical goal in Typeform we want CI in all projects, but currently this only exists for the dev-portal
I'd just work on unifying this more across projects / unifying it with other Typeform colonies but this is a process and right now we're not in a great position to do this (which is okay)
I'd explore using a CMS backend. (Could be Wordpress API or some other service) and then building a decoupled frontend
More tests! :) (but we also need to figure out what is the best way to test our things)

metadata.user_agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_12_6) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/60.0.3112.101 Safari/537.36

answers.text: I think deployment is still pretty simple though not completely automated. I'd like CI in the other projects though.
I dislike the script concatenation and use of Gulp. I would like to move to Webpack at the minimum, with WDS. Ideally, we'd use Gatsby and React components
I would like to move away from Wordpress. Using Gatsby (or any SWG) would be my preference.
I would turn everything into static websites. Remove jQuery and Angular.
I just want easy staging environments and less configuration.
